Date:  0/0/1967
Source:  Kettle on the Fuchsia, The
Author:  HARPER
Vol / Page:  92
Edition:
Quote:  Among all those men in dungarees ... was one man with a high starched collar and tie. Systematically he walked the woolshed floor, saw that every sheep was thoroughly shorn, not a tuft left, and kept an account of the tallies. He was known as `the boss of the boards.'
Notes:

